content.description: Same start as Max Attacks, on the slopey/crimpy rail feature. Goes right along the rail and then up once you reach the arete. I've seen two options at the arete: straight up via the crimp on the arete or up and right to the obvious blocky feature around the corner. Both seem about the same difficulty to me.
content.protection: Pads. Landing is mostly flat but if you choose to go out right around the corner you'll be over some bushes and a fun stab-tastic spike rock. So definitely protect that guy.
content.location: Same boulder as Max Attacks. About halfway between the Yosemite Highball boulder and the Nosebleed boulder there's a trail that heads in the uphill direction. This trail is short and leads to the White Arete boulder which sits directly below a larger boulder with a tall face that you can see from the trail.

content.description: Crux was the start with minimal feet. Fun short climb to a nice mantle, but the crimps are sharp as heck. Start on the well chalked jug in the middle of the face about chest height and work your way up on sharp crimps. Fun mantle but would be much better if the crimps weren't so sharp.
content.protection: Pad or two, mantle wasn't the crux but had some height
content.location: On the trail up to the Mad Max cave. Well chalked sharp incut crimps a couple feet left of the arete. Can't miss it or the north side of the trail (coming to Mad Max from the southeast)
